    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on </span><span class=\"english\">‘Participation of Women in Sports in</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Bangladesh’</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences.    </span><span class=\"english\">10</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span> </span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Participation of Women in Sports in Bangladesh</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Participation of women in sports in Bangladesh has seen remarkable progress in recent decades. However, it continues to face significant challenges stemming from societal and infrastructural shortcomings. The success of female athletes, particularly in football, has shattered traditional gender stereotypes that once confined girls to a limited set of roles.  Teams like the </span><span class=\"english\">Kalsindur</span><span class=\"english\"> girls have not only brought national and international titles but have also become a symbol of girl power and resilience for the entire nation. Despite these achievements, female athletes often face hurdles such as social stigma, lack of adequate training facilities, and unequal pay compared to their male counterparts. Parental and community support, as demonstrated in the </span><span class=\"english\">Kalsindur</span><span class=\"english\"> story, is crucial for aspiring female athletes to overcome these barriers. The government and various sports federations are gradually recognizing the potential of women in sport. Therefore, it will lead to more opportunities and infrastructure development. With continued encouragement and investment, the future of women in sports in Bangladesh looks brighter, promising more victories and empowerment for generations to come. The success of these pioneering women is a testament to their unwavering determination and serves as an inspiration for many.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Participation of Women in Sports in Bangladesh) </span><span class=\"english\">------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Bangladesh has made significant strides in promoting women's participation in sports, but still faces significant challenges due to societal and infrastructural issues.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Female Athlete Success in Bangladesh--------------------------------------------------------------06 Marks</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">• Breaks traditional gender stereotypes in football.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">• Teams like </span><span class=\"english\">Kalsindur</span><span class=\"english\"> symbolize girl power and resilience.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Challenges include social stigma, inadequate training, and unequal pay.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Parental and community support crucial for overcoming barriers.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Government and sports federations recognize women's potential.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Continued encouragement and investment can lead to more opportunities and infrastructure development.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The achievements of these pioneering women are a testament to their unwavering determination and serve as a source of inspiration for many.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), </span><span class=\"english\">full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para).</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Make meaningful sentences using the given words.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>                                    5</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Inhibition, </span><span class=\"english\">Vigour</span><span class=\"english\">, Unleash, Inclusion, Counterpart</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Inhibition – Her </span><span class=\"english\">inhibition</span><span class=\"english\"> prevented her from speaking confidently in front of the audience.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Vigour</span><span class=\"english\"> – The athletes played with great </span><span class=\"english\">vigour</span><span class=\"english\"> despite the exhausting weather conditions.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Unleash – The coach’s speech helped </span><span class=\"english\">unleash</span><span class=\"english\"> the team’s hidden strength and determination.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Inclusion – </span><span class=\"english\">Inclusion</span><span class=\"english\"> of diverse voices makes any discussion richer and more meaningful.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Counterpart – The prime minister is to meet his European </span><span class=\"english\">counterparts</span><span class=\"english\"> to discuss the war against drugs.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><a></a><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for </span><span class=\"english\">01 spelling</span><span class=\"english\"> mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">(iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.)</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
