    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the proverb:</span><span class=\"english\"> “A man is known by the company he keeps.”</span><span><span> </span> </span><span class=\"english\">5</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Our associations reflect our character. The people we choose to spend time with reveal who we are and what we value. For example, someone who regularly associates with honest people will likely be seen as honest. The proverb teaches that we are judged by the company we keep, and our relationships often reflect our personality. The message is that our friendships and associations shape how others perceive us. It encourages people to be mindful of the influences in their lives and choose relationships that align with their values and character.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Theme Of the Proverb </span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Our relationships with others reflect our character, as they reveal who we are and what we value.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Context Explanation </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">) ---------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1</span><span class=\"english\">.Our</span><span class=\"english\"> character is reflected through the people we spend time with.                                                                                                           </span><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">.Associations</span><span class=\"english\"> influence how others judge and perceive us.                                                                                                                               </span><span class=\"english\">3</span><span class=\"english\">.Being</span><span class=\"english\"> around honest and good people helps build a positive reputation.                                                                                          </span><span class=\"english\">4</span><span class=\"english\">.Friendships</span><span class=\"english\"> and relationships reveal our values and personality.                                                                                                                   </span><span class=\"english\">5</span><span class=\"english\">.We</span><span class=\"english\"> should be careful about the kind of people we choose to associate with.                                                                                           </span><span class=\"english\">6</span><span class=\"english\">.Good</span><span class=\"english\"> company helps develop good habits and character.                                                                                                                    </span><span class=\"english\">7</span><span class=\"english\">.The</span><span class=\"english\"> proverb advises choosing companions who inspire positive qualities.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">**For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span><span> </span></p>"
